        "label": "Ordo of 1200",
        "labelFr": "Ordo de 1200",
        "openatlasClass": "E33 Linguistic Object",
        "systemClass": "artifact",
        "viewClass": "artifact",
        "type": "ordo_text",
        "tradition": "OCF",
        "date": "ca. 1200",
        "description": "The last of the 'Frankish' ordines (i.e., displaying few French-specific traits). Essentially a developed version of the Romano-Germanic pontifical's royal ordo. MS A was located in the coronation cathedral at Reims until the Revolution and was demonstrably consulted in later centuries. One of four sources of the Ordo of 1250 (Ordo XXI)."
      }
